DataElement.preferredDefinition: A specified list of terms with a fixed and unalterable meaning, and from which a selection is made when cataloging, indexing, or searching books, journals, and other documents. The control is intended to avoid the scattering of related subjects under different headings.:A word or expression used for some particular thing.:Any factor that defines a system and determines (or limits) its performance.:The information contained in a data field.  It may represent a numeric quantity, a textual characterization, a date or time measurement, or some other state, depending on the nature of the attribute._One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is a long integer (64-bit two's complement).
